The Para gnatcatcher (Polioptila paraensis) or Klages's gnatcatcher, is a species of bird in the family Polioptilidae. It is found in state of Par√° in the southeast Amazonian region of Brazil.
The Para gnatcatcher was formerly treated as a subspecies of the Guianan gnatcatcher (Polioptila guianensis) but is now considered as a separate species based on the difference in morphology and vocalisation.